<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Conger</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Pekin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-03"><hi rend="italic">June 3,
                                1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Outside of Pekin murders and persecutions by Boxers increasing. Paotingfu
                            railway temporarily abandoned. Work on Pekin-Hankow line stopped. All
                            foreigners fled. Chinese Government can not or will not suppress. Troops
                            do not attack Boxers. Relations between the factions of imperial
                            advisers very much strained. General situation very critical.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Conger.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>